ROLE
• Perform quarterly valuation analyses for 44 investments in the "company" family across 4 separate funds; 
o Track incoming information from portfolio companies including financial statements, cap tables, headcount, budgets/plans and 409a reports;
o Ensure accuracy of data uploaded into the valuation software provided by Shareholder InSite;
o Meet with General Partners to discuss preliminary valuation analyses to make sure the results are consistent with board of director level thinking;
o Use software to run outcome scenarios;
o Create and maintain key portfolio metrics and dashboards;
• Assist with compliance for regulatory filings and financings; 
• Assist with internal and external financial reporting;
• Interface with outside accounting services provider regarding invoices and all other fund cash inflows and outflows;
• Maintain cash flow projections for each fund;
• Support the annual external audit process.
KEY REQUIREMENTS
• 3-5 years of work experience with Big 4 or Regional accounting firm; venture capital experience a plus; 
• Genuine interest in becoming proactively involved in managing a large, varied portfolio and working actively with partners to create value; 
• Great Excel skills and basic math capabilities are required.
• Excellent people skills and a good, clear communication style. Effective team player - able to work effectively in a small, established team of seasoned investment professionals. The position requires a high level of independence and responsibility.
